  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink268-kilavi">avaṉ kuṟipp irunta vāṟṟāl nammaip pirintu vant allatu varaiya māṭṭāṉ pōṉṟ iruntat eṉat talaimakaḷ kūṟak kēṭṭa tōḻi yavaṭkut talaimakaṉ ciṟaippuṟattāṉ ākac colliyatu.
          </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">What the confidante said to the heroine, as the hero was behind the hedge; having listened as the heroine said, “From the way he intended, he seemed one who would not marry unless he had separated from us and come.”
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink268">
<l>tāa yiḻanta taḻuvarik kuruḷaiyoṭu</l>
<l>vaḷamalaic ciṟutiṉai yuṇīik kāṉavar</l>
<l>varaiyōṅ kuyarcimaik kēḻa luṟaṅku</l>
<l>naṉmalai nāṭaṉ pirita</l>
<l>leṉpayak kummō namviṭṭut tuṟantē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>How will the separation</l>
        <l>of the man from the land of the good mountain,</l>
        <l>where a boar, having eaten small millet on the fertile mountain,</l>
        <l rend="space">sleeps on the very lofty summit</l>
        <l>of the mountain of the forest people,</l>
        <l>together with its piglets of close stripes</l>
        <l>that have lost their mother—</l>
        <l rend="space">be of any benefit,</l>
        <l>having abandoned us?</l>
        
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
